# propertyCache

**Instance Property**

The property cache dictionary of the node.

## Declaration

```swift
var propertyCache: NSMutableDictionary? { get set }
```

## Discussion

This dictionary is used by [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSAtomicStoreCacheNode/value(forKey:)] and [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSAtomicStoreCacheNode/setValue(_:forKey:)] for property values. This property is `nil` unless it has been explicitly set or non-`nil` values have been set for keys using [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSAtomicStoreCacheNode/setValue(_:forKey:)].

## Managing Node Data

- **objectID**: The managed object ID of the node.
- **value(forKey:)**: Returns the value for a given key.
- **setValue(_:forKey:)**: Sets the value for the given key.
